The paper deals with the construction of non-overlapping sets of pictures, which is a problem in computational geometry (cs.CG). The concept of non-expandable sets is related to combinatorial optimization (cs.DS, cs.DM), and the examples of application mentioned in the paper involve image processing and computer vision (cs.DL, cs.CV).
